<br>
I'd just jump in and see; but only a play a few hours a week and time in-game is kinda valuable - don't want to invest a lot of time in the rp server (would prefer to continue with my mid-teen lvl chanter on the other server).<br>
<br>
Soooo those on the rp server, do you like it?  is the roleplaying done kinda 'intense' or are there a lot of 'flapping out of char' to discuss stuff?<br>
<br>
thanks for any input,<br>
fiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bregaladlow>Bregalad LoW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#330000>(7/25/03 9:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Firiona Vie [roleplay svr] question</span><hr size=1> If you want to check the atmosphere there, just make a character there, and run around a bit.  A night in PoK should give a good indication of how things are.<br>
<br>
Far as I understand, people on FV do not really care about RP more than on other servers, and are playing it more 'for  the challenge and the difference'.<br>
<br>
IMO, the silly set of rules on FV in no way promotes roleplay.    I would not touch that server with a 10-foot pole, honestly.  If you want to RP, don't be in a hurry to shell out $50 to SOE - shop around your current server for an RP guild. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
