<br>
I can not think of any game or any server where a majority of the population roll plays after the first 6 months.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loriwen>Loriwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(7/25/03 6:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Firiona Vie [roleplay svr] question</span><hr size=1> Despite opinions to the contrary, roleplay is not dead on FV.  It has lessened from the intensity it used to be at, but that is mainly because the softening of the ruleset brought an influx of people who wanted to benefit from the lack of NO DROP.  People aren't there for the challenge, they are either there to roleplay or to get phat lewtz.  (With few scattered others who might actually be there for different reasons.)<br>
<br>
There are still several strong roleplaying guilds that run events, create storylines and interact in character the majority of the time they deal with others.  I'd suggest going here first ...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie">pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Read up.  Check out some of the wonderful stories players have created about their characters.  Follow the links in the Guild section and look at how important they consider roleplay to be.  Then, once you've looked around a bit, create a character, throw enough detail on them to know how you'd like to roleplay and then enter the world.  <br>
<br>
You will run into those that don't RP.  Especially in your lower levels.  But, if RP is what you want, this is the only place I know of to find it in EQ.  Look for those that roleplay, interact with them.  Find members of the guilds you noted and interact with them.  Play, have fun, etc.<br>
<br>
You may come to love it.  You may drift back to whatever else you'd been doing before.<br>
<br>
As far as I've seen, Roleplay is dead, buried and the grave has been danced over on the majority of EQ.  On FV, it is still going strong. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:edwardian script itc;font-size:x-large;">Loriwen Tathrenlin</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:edwardian script itc;font-size:large;">High Elf Phantasmist</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-family:ms sans serif;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370372">My Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black face;font-size:x-small;">Member of</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.everarchangel.com"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:ms sans serif;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The Archangel</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-family:ms sans serif;font-size:x-small;">on Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
